**What is git ignore?
gitignore file tells Git which files to ignore when committing your project to the GitHub repository. 
gitignore is located in the root directory of your repo.The .gitignore file itself is a plain text document.

--To create a .gitignore file use below command
$touch .gitignore
-to ignore README.txt file - $echo "README.txt">>.gitignore
-to ignore any .java file - $echo "*.java">>.gitignore
-if you want to ignore any folder for example output - $echo "output/">>.gitignore


step 2 : Check the git status, Now if you try to add those files to the git repository it will be ignored.
$git status
